Comments? Email us at or call us at What is your pricing and what does it include? Our Essential plan starts at $20 month and includes two automation processes each A process is when you apply one of our tools (e.g., mesh creation, texture optimization, point cloud cleaning, etc) to your uploaded Our Advanced ($30 month) and Professional ($100 month) plans allow for more processes with larger file sizes and are great for business We also offer Enterprise plans for companies who have custom needs, such as full API access and dedicated support Please see our Pricing page for a list of each plan s Are you interested in our Enterprise plan? Please contact , and we ll be in touch How do you define a process? We define a process as applying one of our automation tools (e.g., mesh creation, texture optimization, point cloud cleaning, and more) to your You can apply multiple processes to a single file or a single process to multiple How often am I billed? Subscriptions are billed every As an example, if you were to start your paid subscription on January , your next two billing cycles would be February and then again on March New automation processes are also added to your account on those What payment options do you accepted for subscriptions? We use PayPal to process all monthly The PayPal platform accepts a large number of credit and debit cards such as Visa, Mastercard, American Express, and In addition, PayPal also offers bank account Please note that you need to link a card or link a bank to your account before you can select it as a preferred way to When do I get new automation processes added to my account? New processes are added to your account every days on your billing I didn t use all my processes this month, will they rollover? At this time we do not offer the ability to rollover unused monthly How do I update my billing information? Please update your new credit card information, billing address, and payment methods through your PayPal To get started, click here . How do I change or cancel my subscription? If you d like to upgrade, downgrade, or cancel your account, please do so through your Account Settings on our Note that cancellations must be made days in advance of your next For example, if your last payment was on April and you decided to cancel your account on April , you would still be billed on May and have access to your account and your allotted automation processes through June If you cancel your account, you will have access to your remaining files until they expire in accordance with your plan, but you will not have access to MOD s automation tools and services after your cancellation In what countries can I purchase a subscription? Industry Outlook Join us News Contact Us Our Technology LiNiCo s Green battery recycling technology produces % pure battery Battery Rejuvenation batteries (LIBs) have been the preferred portable energy source in recent The exponential growth in the use of LIBs for EVs, as a choice in energy storage and consumer devices has resulted in a great number of spent Disposal of these spent LIBs will cause serious environmental problems due to hazardous components such as heavy metals and The current battery recycling methods are not suitable for LIB recycling due to its slow process, low purity of the products (low profits) and the use of friendly leaching Materials contained in the spent LIBs are valuable resources and can be recycled by using our specific Our Battery Recycling Technology Our Battery recycling technology is based on a process and control system which can process various types of spent These include: Lithium cobalt oxide (LCO) Lithium manganese oxide (LMO) Lithium nickel manganese cobalt oxide (NMC) Lithium nickel cobalt aluminium oxide (NCA). The method allows the recovery of cathode metal salts in their original form, without separation of the metal The obtained metal salts could then serve as the precursor for synthesis of new cathode The technology we are using recovers the following products at more than % purity levels: (a) Graphite and (b) Cathode metal salts LiCo1 3Ni1 3Mn1 3O2, NiCO3, MnCO3, CoC2O4, and Producing pure battery grade material to Features & Specifications The method avoids separation of the cathode metal elements, saving cost and reduces processing In contrary, traditional separation of Co and Ni metals by solvent extraction from NMC batteries involve complicated steps and is a slow Moreover, the separated cobalt (Co) and nickel (Ni) salts are mixed again for the synthesis of new cathode Various types of LIB can be processed and valuable cathode precursors can be Greener â€“ Zero toxic discharge, zero landfill, lower reliance on Purer â€“ The end product is % pure and is therefore of better value to a battery producing Faster â€“ This method is faster than traditional battery recycling technology because it processes ALL of the Output â€“ Immediately Battery Cathodes Outlook & Opportunities Over the next years to , the global battery recycling market size is expected to grow a staggering 1,107% to USD $18.7 Billion The North American market is forecast to account for % of the global battery recycling market by , with a Compound Annual Growth Rate (CAGR) of %. TheraHive: DBT Course Details Our Courses FAQs Sign In Join a FREE Info Session < Back to Courses Dialectical Behavioral Therapy (DBT) Skills Course Overview 6 Month Complete Path: Delivered in 4 sections with weekly curriculum and live Orientation Session: A orientation session that introduces you to our platform and prepares you for your learning Assessments & Graduation: An assessment is completed at the end of each section (4 total) and a certificate is awarded for successful completion of the 1:1 Coaching: An optional addition for students who miss a live session or that need additional Join Course Course Creator Alicia Smart Board of Certification certified therapist Our unique approach to learning DBT Skills Smart Watch the Video 2:38 "TheraHive is great, online group learning is long IÃ¢Â€Â™d recommend the DBT course to almost anyone who didnÃ¢Â€Â™t master some basic life skills earlier in life!" Cutting Works CK Rail safely completed over 6,500 hours of emergency work to repair and strengthen a railway cutting at Hever station in Engineers were onsite within two hours of reports a landslip had occurred south of platform 1 at the station on the Uckfield branch of the Oxted An initial incident survey and report identified significant ground movement had occurred and there was evidence of slope CK Rail were appointed to complete the essential work to secure the cutting and ensure the railway line could safely remain Excellent collaborative working between CK Rail, client Dyer and Butler, the Works Delivery team at Network Rail and local landowners enabled this emergency project to be completed as efficiently and safely as CK Rail engineers worked with a local farmer to agree the installation of a temporary haulage road through farmland to the site and this was created sustainably, using recycled This temporary access enabled plant, machinery and materials to be safely transported to and from site, maximising the overall efficiency of the work carried Fencing was also erected to ensure the safe segregation of livestock from the haulage road and The cutting was monitored for earth movement throughout the duration of the Before the core remedial works could commence a buried services search of the area revealed a UK Power Networks electricity cable was present along the crest of the Following a site visit between CK Rail engineers and UK Power Networks representatives, protective safety measures were implemented, including relocating the proposed piling location to ensure a safe working distance from the existing services The core works included clearing and removing a total of tonnes of spoil material from the Engineers then implemented the agreed engineering design solution which included the installation of a king post wall to retain the slope, embedded below ground level to secure the A piling platform was created using piles driven into the ground, installed at the crest of the slope and a retaining wall was constructed at the toe of the cutting with gabion baskets erected and filled with 1,605 tonnes of gabion The slope was also regraded to provide further On completion of this vital work, demobilisation of the site commenced, including comprehensive remedial work to reinstate the surrounding Engineers installed of new fencing and planted two oak trees and silver birch CK Rail were delighted to have safely and successfully completed these emergency earthworks, ensuring a safer, more reliable and sustainable rail
